<font color="#FF0000">GOOD RIVER!</font><br>
<tt>Mon Aug 11  4:00:39 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
John:  <br>
Like you, the river is a good brother.  Also, like you and me it gets contaminated and must purge itself.  This brother can be angry and turbulent, smooth and quiet, clear or murky.  Strong rivers give life... and take life. Where they are blocked by right or wrong, they cut a new channel. Always, they are dynamic and changing.  As you comfort me and I comfort you... the river will comfort all who go there seeking.<br>
Wepola is a give away.  We are given many things... and we too give away many things.  Some troubled warriors would give away everything they owned to someone they chose to insult and walk away naked in the cold... just to prove that they could rise again by the strength of their backs, wisdom and most of all, their spirits.  It seems to be the epitomy of telling misfortune, &quot;You cannot hurt me!&quot;  It was the ultimate mockery of bad circumstance.  It wasn't arrogance...but an affirmation...&quot;that you can't keep a good man down!&quot;<br><br>
I will not leave you on the battlefields of Viet Nam... nor will I forsake you on the battlefields of the mind.  You are a Dog Soldier... Akicita Was'te, a good warrior.  You are my spiritual brother.  Was'te Lo!... a condition of greatness.<br><br>
As the number of gray hairs in my head grows larger... the necessary number of arrows in my quiver grows fewer.  Wisdom is the greatest weapon... and you are well armed.<br><br>
Humming Eagle
